                      <p>Vellum, about 8 5/8 in. by 6 1/2, consisting of 155 leaves, some of which
                        are much stained and torn, especially foll. 4—6, 39, 137, 138, 141,143, 144,
                        and 153—155. The quires, signed with letters, were probably about 30 in
                        number; but<foreign xml:lang="syr"> ܐ,ܒ , ܓ,</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="syr">(ܟܒ) ܟܓ </foreign>are lost, and several others are very
